 \frac1{\sqrt{x(1-x)}} = \frac1{\sqrt{1/4 - (x-1/2)^2}} = \frac2{\sqrt{1-(2x-1)^2}}. 
\sin^{-1}(2x-1)+\pi/2 = 2\sin^{-1}(\sqrt x)
